f=Cybersecurity/bastion/custom/cloud-posture/assets/cspm-checklist.md · h1:Cloud Posture Checklist bastion/cloud-posture=Check against CIS Benchmark provider best-practices (dated). bastion detects specs; operator/ops remediates. Prioritize exposure data-sensitivity (veil). · h2:classic high-blast misconfigs (every scan)=public storage buckets/blobs holding non-public data, databases admin ports open 0.0.0.0/0, Security groups firewall rules least-open (no broad ingress), Cloud IAM least-privilege (no `*:*` over-broad roles) keyring seam, Encryption rest enabled (volumes, buckets, DBs), Audit logging cloud-trail enabled retained, Root org-owner accounts MFA; root used routinely, long-lived access keys roles/short-lived secrets-governance) · h2:Prioritize=\| Finding \| Resource \| Exposure (public/internal) \| Data sensitivity (veil) \| Severity \| Fix spec → executor \| · h2:Prioritize=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h2:Prioritize=\| <FILL_IN> \| \| \| \| \| operator / ops gate \| · h2:Drift=Previously-fixed misconfigs re-checked (reappearance process gap, finding), Provider baseline as-of date: [dated cloud services change] Risks warden register